  "gameplayNotes": [
    "pixel-platformer uses 18x18 tiles and 24x24 characters; platformer-pack-redux uses 128x128 tiles and 128x256 characters",
    "For simple walk animation, alternate between idle and walk sprites",
    "Use left/mid/right tile variants to build ground and platform edges properly",
    "Deep tiles (e.g., ground-grass-deep-mid) go below surface tiles to fill underground areas",
    "Enemies in pixel-platformer have 2-frame animations (e.g., slime-1, slime-2)",
    "Coin spinning animation uses coin-spin-1, coin-spin-2, coin-spin-3",
    "Doors and flags consist of top and bottom/mid segments that should be stacked vertically",
    "HD pack aliens have full state sets: stand, walk1, walk2, jump, duck, hit, climb1, climb2, swim1, swim2",
    "Springs switch between compressed and extended states when the player bounces",
    "Use the HUD sprites from platformer-pack-redux for health, keys, and score display"
  ],

